This is the README file for the EvtGen package

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Please send questions to:
David Lange lange@slac.stanford.edu
Anders Ryd ryd@hep.caltech.edu

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

This is release alpha-00-09-42
It is supported on OSF, Linux, and SunOS. Other unix
platforms should be straight forward, in the past we have 
run his code on AIX and HP-UX also, but it is not tested for
this release.

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

The package is documented on the WWW page:

http://www.slac.stanford.edu/~lange/EvtGen/

The documentation is maintained in the directory doc in this
package. Please see doc/README for further information.

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

To get started with EvtGen:

  - Run the "configure" script in this directory.  

  - "gmake" will compile the EvtGen source code and create
    libEvtGen.a

  - "gmake bin" will build the executable testEvtGen which
    can be run from the "test" subdirectory with the command
    "../testEvtGen test1 1000" this executable has a C++ driver.

  - Additional information can be found in the documentation.

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

